    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "How long does the scan take?",
        "answer": "About 15 minutes, including positioning.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is the test painful?",
        "answer": " No. You simply lie still; no needles or injections.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive home afterwards?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you requested sedation.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I feel claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "We offer wide-bore 70 cm MRI & music of your choice; mild sedation on request."
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon will I get results?",
        "answer": "Digital report and images within 2 hours of scan completion.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What's the difference between a plain MRI and one without contrast?",
        "answer": "These terms are often used interchangeably. A plain MRI neck scan refers to an MRI of the neck performed without the injection of any contrast material, just like an MRI Neck Without Contrast. "
      }
